column16:
SNAP Outreach at Food Bank Council of Michigan
>>>>>>> master
April 15 at 2:21 PM ·

The Michigan Department of Health and Human Services recently announced a new program: Pandemic EBT.

The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer Program (P-EBT) program provides temporary funding to address emergency food needs for families affected by the COVID-19 pandemic.

P-EBT food assistance benefits will go to Michigan families with students ages 5-18 that are eligible for free or reduced-price school meals. This includes families currently receiving Food Assistance Program benefits, as well as those not currently enrolled in the program. No application is necessary for eligible families to receive P-EBT benefits.

Please see flyer below for more details on the program.

Full press release: https://www.michigan.gov/coronavirus/0,9753,7-406-98158-525248--,00.html

post_text:
Hello all K-8th grade parents,
Now that your children have been home for a few days, are you thinking they just need to learn a little more? They really could use some more support in math or reading to be set for this fall? We have an opportunity to offer you free tutoring from Sylvan learning company right here on our campus this summer. This opportunity is paid for through our state funding and is being offered to 62 of our elementary and middle school students on a first come first serve basis. The tutoring will run 4 days a week after our summer school program ends, from 1:35 -3:05 pm for 6 weeks straight. Students have to take a placement test given by Sylvan to see their level and target their needed support.

If you are interested, please contact
Ms. Castle immediately! Leave her a message with your child’s name, grade, and parent contact number.

Call Ms. Castle today at 810.591.9276. Stay tuned for more opportunities
